and gateway to scholarship and high culture, and the hybrid realities of German North America where the lives of migrants were shaped by two languages, English and German. Theirs was a song not of cultural purity, but of cultural fusion that gave meaning to the way German migrants made a home for themselves in North America.Written in lively and elegant prose, Sounds of Ethnicity is a new and exciting approach to the history of immigration and identity in North America.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aGerman AmericansxEthnic identity. 0aGerman AmericansxLanguagesxNorth AmericaxGreat Lakes Region (North America). 0aGerman AmericansxMusicxNorth AmericaxGreat Lakes Region (North America). 0aGerman AmericansxSocial life and customsxNorth AmericaxGreat Lakes Region (North America). 0aGerman AmericanszNorth AmericazGreat Lakes Region (North America)xLanguages. 0aGerman AmericanszNorth AmericazGreat Lakes Region (North America)xMusic. 0aGerman AmericanszNorth AmericazGreat Lakes Region (North America)xSocial life and customs. 0aGerman CanadiansxLanguagesxNorth AmericaxGreat Lakes Region (North America). 0aGerman CanadiansxMusicxNorth AmericaxGreat Lakes Region (North America). 0aGerman CanadiansxSocial life and customsxNorth AmericaxGreat Lakes Region (North America). 0aGerman CanadianszNorth AmericazGreat Lakes Region (North America)xLanguages. 0aGerman CanadianszNorth AmericazGreat Lakes Region (North America)xMusic. 0aGerman CanadianszNorth AmericazGreat Lakes Region (North America)xSocial life and customs. 7aHISTORY / Canada / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2011-2010z978311127414008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2011 - 2010z978311127721940uhttps://doi